Depuis ses dbuts en 1999, le Canadian Guitar Quartet sest produit sur trois continents, enchanant les ovations debout et se forgeant une rputation comme lun des meilleurs ensembles de guitares au monde.

Au cours de ses plus de vingt ans dexistence, le CGQ a lanc quatre albums salus par la critique tout en menant de nombreuses tournes au Canada et  ltranger, se produisant autant en rcital quavec orchestre. Leur premier concert au 92nd Street Y  New York, dans le cadre de la srie
Art of the Guitar

, a t accueilli avec un immense enthousiasme. Don Witter Jr., de la New York City Classical Guitar Society, a crit :  Le Canadian Guitar Quartet a offert lun des dbuts les plus marquants  New York pour un ensemble artistique depuis des dcennies POUSTOUFLANT !!!
En plus de se produire sur scne et denregistrer, le CGQ continue de soutenir la relve en guitare en offrant des ateliers, des classes de matre et un enseignement personnalis.

Mme si la composition du groupe a volu au fil des ans, lensemble reste fidle  sa mission premire : offrir de la musique de chambre au plus haut niveau, avec un savant mlange de nouvelles adaptations duvres classiques et de crations audacieuses pour quatuor de guitares  souvent crites par danciens ou actuels membres du groupe. Un rpertoire captivant, interprt avec une virtuosit flamboyante et une complicit chaleureuse avec le public : voil ce qui fait de chaque concert du Canadian Guitar Quartet un moment inoubliable.

Since its debut in 1999, the Canadian Guitar Quartet has performed on three continents, going from one standing ovation to the next, and established a reputation as one of the finest guitar ensembles in the world.

During its twenty-plus years, the CGQ has released four critically acclaimed albums while touring extensively in Canada and abroad, appearing in recital, and with orchestra. The CGQ's first concert at the 92Street Y in New York city, part of the Art of the Guitar series, was extremely well received. Don Witter Jr., of the New York City Classical Guitar Society, wrote: "The Canadian Guitar Quartet made one of the greatest New York City Debuts of any artistic ensemble in decadesSTUNNING !!!".
As well as performing and recording, the CGQ continues to mentor and direct young guitarists through clinics, masterclasses, and one on one teaching.

While personnel changes have occurred over the years, the ensemble has remained committed to its core mission: chamber music at its highest level, presenting a robust mix of clever new arrangements of classical masterworks alongside bold new works for guitar quartet  most often penned by past and present members of the ensemble. The engaging repertoire, performed with the CGQ's fiery virtuosity, augmented by the players' easy and congenial rapport with the audience, all make a Canadian Guitar Quartet concert an event to remember.

The Canadian Guitar Quartet (CGQ) is set to captivate audiences with an upcoming special concert that promises a rich and diverse musical experience. The program features an exciting blend of original compositions and celebrated pieces from the Brazilian repertoire, along with a touch of Mozart. Attendees can look forward to the quartet's interpretation of Mozart's Sonata K.V. 448, showcasing their technical prowess and harmonious synergy. The concert also includes 'Pulsar' by Olga Amelkina-Vera and 'Empty Houses' by Renaud Ct-Gigure, offering contemporary explorations of the guitar's expressive range. Additionally, the quartet will perform arrangements of Brazilian classics such as 'Areias Brancas' and selections from 'Orfeu Negro' by Antonio Carlos Jobim and Luis Bonfa, infusing the evening with rhythmic vitality and melodic charm. This thoughtfully curated program exemplifies CGQ's commitment to delivering performances that are both engaging and artistically enriching.
About the Carmel Guitar Society

Founded in 1961, Carmel Guitar Society is one of the oldest classical guitar societies existing today. Dedicated to education, community, and performance, the organization presents events throughout Monterey Bay that bring community members together.

The Carmel Guitar Society fosters classical guitar appreciation and cultural enrichment in Monterey County through concerts, workshops, and therapeutic music programs. By supporting local and international artists, offering accessible ticket programs, and providing educational workshops, the organization brings the community together to experience, enjoy, and celebrate the beauty of classical guitar.

Taking place in Gatineau and Ottawa from February 26 to March 2, with performances and events at venues including the Conservatoire de musique de Gatineau, the University of Ottawas Tabaret Hall, and glise Notre-Dame-de-la-Guadeloupe, this anniversary edition promises an exceptional program featuring a mix of concerts, master classes, and conferences led by some of the worlds most celebrated guitarists.

We are thrilled to join the lineup for the 2024/2025 season of the Peninsula International Guitar Series, with concerts held at First Lutheran Church and All Saints Church in Palo Alto. This season will showcase the renowned and versatile guitarist Dieter Hennings, the captivating Duo Chinoiserie, the dynamic Chattanooga Guitar Duo, and the 4th Annual SFCM Guitar Student Showcase. We look forward to welcoming you to a season of exceptional performances.

The Peninsula Guitar Series is dedicated to bringing the classical guitar to the Peninsulas diverse community, bridging the gap between the concert hall and new audiences. Since 2012, we have presented local, emerging, and international guitarists to perform in concert and to provide educational activities furthering the appreciation of the guitar in the Bay Area. As ambassadors of the guitar, we seek to enrich and strengthen the lives of those we touch through our vibrant classical guitar community of concertgoers, exemplary artists, and dedicated educators.

This season will showcase the renowned and versatile guitarist Dieter Hennings, the captivating Duo Chinoiserie, the dynamic Chattanooga Guitar Duo, and the 4th Annual SFCM Guitar Student Showcase. We look forward to welcoming you to a season of exceptional performances.

The Peninsula Guitar Series is dedicated to bringing the classical guitar to the Peninsulas diverse community, bridging the gap between the concert hall and new audiences. Since 2012, we have presented local, emerging, and international guitarists to perform in concert and to provide educational activities furthering the appreciation of the guitar in the Bay Area. As ambassadors of the guitar, we seek to enrich and strengthen the lives of those we touch through our vibrant classical guitar community of concertgoers, exemplary artists, and dedicated educators.

Join the Canadian Guitar Quartet for a spellbinding evening of music that travels through time and across continents. This special performance will feature a rich tapestry of worksfrom fiery Spanish dances and lyrical Romantic-era gems to dynamic new compositions written specifically for the ensemble.

With their signature blend of precision, passion, and playful charisma, the CGQ will bring to life music by composers such as Manuel de Falla, Claude Debussy, and contemporary Canadian talents. Whether you're a lifelong classical guitar enthusiast or new to the genre, this concert promises an unforgettable experience of musical storytelling and ensemble brilliance.
Come discover why the Canadian Guitar Quartet continues to captivate audiences worldwidefour guitars, one breathtaking voice.
About the Festival of the Sound

The Festival of the Sound is a world-renowned chamber and classical music festival in scenic Parry Sound. Founded in 1979 by pianist Anton Kuerti, The Festival has grown to cover three weeks and dozens of concerts, including weekends of jazz and folk music. The concerts take place in the
Charles W. Stockey Centre
, with special events like cruises and masterclasses using other local venues such as the
Island Queen Cruise Ship
or the Festival Station Office.
What began as a small concert in Parry Sound in 1979 has now become one of the premier summer festivals in Canada, with performances by some of the worlds finest musicians and conductors.
